<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-07-02T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-07-02T03:00:00-05:00" n="94" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d94">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">124.83/89: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-07-02T11:00:00+03:00">July 2,
                                    1942—11 a.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received July 2—5:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1133. Department’s 649, June 30, 11 p.m. As already reported by me the
                            question has been raised as to an eventual departure of the Egyptian
                            Government and the British Ambassador has suggested removal to Khartoum.
                            Up to last night no decision had been taken by Egyptian Government
                            although as previously stated there are indications that it would
                            remain.</p>
                        <p>I had assumed that upon leaving Egypt my ultimate destination would be
                            Jidda pending further dispositions.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Kirk</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>